      {
        "question": "Which platforms are supported for model strings?",
        "answer": "All major Anthropic integration platforms are supported: Anthropic API (1P), AWS Bedrock, Google Vertex AI, and Azure AI Foundry."
      },
      {
        "question": "What is the effort parameter and why is it set to high?",
        "answer": "Effort controls how eagerly Claude spends tokens for reasoning. High effort provides the best performance for complex tasks and is recommended for Opus 4.5."
      },
      {
        "question": "Does this skill access my credentials or API keys?",
        "answer": "No, this skill only reads and modifies model string references in code. It does not access credentials, authentication tokens, or external services."
      },
      {
        "question": "What if Opus 4.5 behaves differently after migration?",
        "answer": "The skill includes prompt adjustment snippets for common issues like tool overtriggering, over-engineering, and thinking sensitivity. Apply these only if users report specific problems."
      },
      {
        "question": "How is this different from just searching and replacing model strings?",
        "answer": "This skill provides comprehensive migration including beta header handling, effort parameter configuration, and known behavioral fixes that improve Opus 4.5 compatibility."
